<P><H1 align=center>PERSONAL DETAILS – DC030</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields shown in 
red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT></P>
<P><H3>Name, title and date of birth: </H3>are carried over 
from <A HREF="HELP_CR020.asp">Customer Details (CR020)</A>, where they were previously input. These fields 
must be completed to proceed so ensure all the relevant details have been 
carried over
<P></P>
<P><H3>Nationality: </H3>this field must be completed to 
proceed, so select the appropriate nationality from the dropdown list Resident 
in the UK?: this is also mandatory, if If the applicant is not UK resident the 
application may not be able to proceed (depending on the <A HREF="HELP_MortgageTerms.asp#LendingCriteria">lending criteria</A> – see 
<A HREF="HELP_DC012.asp">Application Verification DC012</A>). Tick the ‘Yes’ or ‘No’ radio button as 
appropriate.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Member of staff?: </H3>this must also be completed. If 
the applicant is a member of staff, there may be special conditions with regard 
to the product or fees payable
<P></P>
<P><H3>Smoker / Good Health?: </H3>these fields must also be 
completed. If the applicant is requiring a quotation for life cover, the cost of 
cover or whether it is available at all may depend on these factors. If the 
applicant is not in good health further medical evidence may be required, or the 
application for life cover may be declined.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Marital status: </H3>select the applicant’s marital 
status from the drop-down list. If it is a sole application and the applicant is 
married / cohabiting and the partner is to be resident in the property but not 
be party to the mortgage., then a consent to mortgage form may need to be 
completed., if the partner is to be resident in the property but not be party to 
the mortgage.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Do you / will you have sufficient life cover in place at time of taking out 
the mortgage?: </H3>life cover is an important factor to 
consider when taking out a mortgage. Although most lenders no longer take 
assignment of life policies, they need to ensure that they have highlighted the 
issue of life cover. Depending on the <A HREF="HELP_MortgageTerms.asp#LendingCriteria">lending criteria</A>, it may be necessary for 
the applicant to confirm that they will have life cover in place before a 
mortgage offer can be made.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Previous Names: </H3>if the applicant has changed their 
name in the past, click on the ‘Previous Names’ button, and this leads to <A HREF="HELP_DC033.asp">Alias 
/ Association Details – DC033</A>.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Verification: </H3>once the details have been entered, 
click on the ‘Verification’ button. This leads to <A HREF="HELP_DC031.asp">Verification Details (DC031)</A>.
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK:</H3>click on ‘OK’ to proceed to the next screen, 
<A HREF="HELP_DC040.asp">Dependant Summary (DC040)</A>
<P></P>

